<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Lab notebook — {{PROJECT_NAME}}</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="research.css">
</head>
<!-- LAB NOTEBOOK — the human-readable research history (analog of SDD history.html).
     Reverse-chronological: newest entry first. 3–6 lines per entry: what ran, what
     happened, what's next. The scribe appends an entry whenever an experiment
     changes state (launched, results in, verdict confirmed, failed, abandoned).
     A copy of research.css/research.js lives in this notebook/ folder. -->
<body>
<div class="page-wrap">

  <nav class="sidebar" aria-label="Table of contents">
    <div class="sidebar-brand">
      <div class="sidebar-brand-name">{{PROJECT_SHORT_NAME}}
        <span>lab notebook</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="sidebar-title">Contents</p>
    <div id="toc-list"></div>
  </nav>

  <div class="main-content">
    <header class="spec-header">
      <h1>Lab notebook — {{PROJECT_NAME}}</h1>
      <p>Dated entries, newest first. Each records what ran, what happened, and
         what's next. Decisions go to <code>decisions/</code>; per-run detail to the
         experiment card; this is the running narrative that ties them together.</p>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section id="entries">
        <h2>Entries</h2>

        <!-- ENTRY FORMAT — copy this block for each event, fill it in, and insert
             it immediately AFTER the INSERT-ENTRY-HERE marker (newest first).
             Remove the "No entries yet" paragraph when adding the first entry.

        <div class="history-entry">
          <div class="history-date">YYYY-MM-DD</div>
          <p><strong>E001 — what changed.</strong> One short paragraph: what ran
             (or was launched/analyzed), what happened (metrics, failure, surprise),
             and what's next. Link the card: <a href="../experiments/E001_slug/card.html">E001</a>.</p>
        </div>

        -->

        <!-- INSERT-ENTRY-HERE -->

        <p style="color: var(--text-muted); font-style: italic;">No entries yet. The first entry is usually the onboarding summary or the first baseline-reproduction card.</p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</div>
<script src="research.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
